<paragraphs xml:id="angle-sum-identities">
  <title>The Angle Sum Identities</title>
    <p>
      If <m>\theta</m> and <m>\phi</m> are angles, then we have
      <md>
        <mrow>\sin(\theta+\phi) \amp = \sin(\theta)\cos(\phi) + \cos(\theta)\sin(\phi) </mrow>
        <mrow>\sin(\theta-\phi) \amp = \sin(\theta)\cos(\phi) - \cos(\theta)\sin(\phi) </mrow>
        <mrow>\cos(\theta+\phi)\amp = \cos(\theta)\cos(\phi) - \sin(\theta)\sin(\phi)  </mrow>
        <mrow>\cos(\theta-\phi)\amp = \cos(\theta)\cos(\phi) + \sin(\theta)\sin(\phi)  </mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
</paragraphs>

